The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Monday, May 10, 2004 				 Healthy lifestyle wards off killer
A cancer patient undergoes radiotherapy at a treatment centre. Pictures by Kishor Roy ChowdhurySujit Kr Dey: Is there any specific method to avoid cancer?																																																													There are no rigid guidelines to avoid the disease, but there are some golden rules by practising which, one may reduce the chance of being afflicted with it. Cancer is directly linked with lifestyle. A healthy way of living is the ideal way to ward off the disease. Quit consuming any form of tobacco, or any type of stimulant, on a regular basis. Excessive intake of animal fat and protein also increases the chances of cancer. A fibrous diet of green vegetables and fruits is advisable. One should also try to keep in shape. Women should take special care in personal hygiene to avoid cervix cancer.
